Kericho County governor, Paul Chepkwony, has revealed of plans to lay an artificial track at the Kericho Green Stadium next year.He said the county government will fund the project to a tune of Sh340m. The governor was speaking during Athletic Kenya (AK) South Rift athletics championships.AK South Rift chairman John Wachira said like other regions, Kericho Green Stadium will now be able to host national and international events. During the one-day event, the region picked 45 athletes to represent them at the national championship slated for Nairobi between June 8-10.The meet attracted hosts Kericho, Bomet, Nakuru, Narok, Laikipia and Kajiado counties.